# WattWise AI Rules

- Follow `AGENTS.md` first.
- Use `skills/spec-driven-development/SKILL.md` before unclear features.
- Use `skills/test-driven-development/SKILL.md` for behavior, calculation, validation, and bug changes.
- Use `skills/incremental-implementation/SKILL.md` for multi-file or risky work.
- Use `skills/code-review-and-quality/SKILL.md` before finishing.
- Use frontend/browser/performance skills for App Router UI work.
- Do not print secrets, modify `.gitignore`, or commit unless explicitly requested.
- Prefer existing stack: Next.js, React, TypeScript, Tailwind, Prisma, NextAuth, Zod, React Hook Form.
- Keep business data scoped to the authenticated user and active business.
